channel.description:
OK so i have a linksys router. I think i got it right but no-ip wont work can someone tell me whats wrong?
In a tut it says to put my def gateaway and at the end there is a 1, when i put that on the portforwarding it says i cant use it. So i put a 2. will this still work?

item.title: Portforwarding/No-Ip help needed!
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

okay let me do this

First Open Up Cmd And Then Type “ipconfig”
okay 3 things should come up

Ip adress: 192.168.* <---- your computers ip
subnet mask:
default gateway:192.168.1 <---- Routers Ip

all you do is type your computers ip number on your port forward
and it should work

item.title: Portforwarding/No-Ip help needed!
item.dc:creator: @durial12 durial12
item.description:
@durial12 wrote:

It says your ip address is 192.168.1.102, try putting that as well. When you get a no-ip, make sure it is redirecting to your normal ip (Normally 92.xx.xx.xx i think). In my case, i cannot log in with my no-ip thing, other people can, i have to log in with 0.0.0.0. Ask a friend to try it out.

Hope this helps!

Durial
